Process of creating tables in Room

1. Define @Entity class
Use @Entity annotation to mark a class as a database table.
Each property in the class is a column in the table.
Use @PrimaryKey to identify the primary key.
Can customize table or column names using @Entity attributes.

2. Declare @Dao
Create interface or abstract class to define database operation methods (CRUD: Create, Read, Update, Delete).

3. Create RoomDatabase class
Use @Database to mark the database management class.
Specify @Entity classes (tables) and database version.

4. Room will automatically create tables when initializing the database